  </ul>

  <h2>Key Terms</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>FiO₂:</strong> Fraction of inspired oxygen — the percentage of oxygen in inhaled air (room air = 21%).</li>
    <li><strong>SpO₂:</strong> Peripheral oxygen saturation measured by pulse oximetry.</li>
    <li><strong>Hypoxia:</strong> Insufficient oxygen at the tissue level.</li>
    <li><strong>Hypoxemia:</strong> Insufficient oxygen in the blood (SpO₂ &lt; 90% or PaO₂ &lt; 60 mmHg).</li>
    <li><strong>Hypercapnia:</strong> Elevated CO₂ in the blood — sign of inadequate ventilation.</li>
    <li><strong>Hypoxic drive:</strong> Respiratory stimulus from low O₂ levels (rather than elevated CO₂) in certain COPD patients.</li>
  </ul>
